$interpreted: Manor Lord: What a grand entrance... You must be the thief that sent that letter?
Naive Princess: Whew, finally found you! Looks like you've been waiting here for me.
Naive Princess: Sorry I didn't have any time to tell you this morning...
Naive Princess: The diamond doesn't need to be all that big... about as big as that Christmas tree's star is fine with me.
Naive Princess: ...Agh, I'm really not ready to be a wife, yet!
Mystery Man: Tricking the princess to fall in love with me like this... Alas, what kind of man am I?
Mystery Man: The Star of True Love...
Mystery Man: Too bad I'm not planning on giving it to anyone!
Manor Lord: Eh!? How'd you know that tree's star was really this manor's precious jewel, the Star of True Love!? Somebody, help! Come apprehend this man!

Mystery Man: I really must thank you for your naivety! Farewell now, princess!
~ Via Love.
Naive Princess: Eh!? How'd you know I was really a princess!?
Naive Princess: ...Oh man! Am I destined to never find true love?
Naive Princess: Ugh... Even mom and dad totally ignored my Christmas list...
Naive Princess: That's it! I'm never trusting storybooks again!
Heroic Knight: Ah... Princess...
Naive Princess: Don't you try and make me feel better! It's no use!
Heroic Knight: No, ah... actually...
Heroic Knight: Forgive me, but, it was me... I changed your Christmas list.
Naive Princess: I said don't try and make me...
Naive Princess: ...Wait, what!?
Naive Princess: So you're the reason we got into this whole mess in the first place!?
Heroic Knight: If I hadn't, I'm sure your parents would have gotten you a cute guy...
Heroic Knight: But I know how easily you fall in love... I didn't want to see you get hurt again.
Heroic Knight: And also... well, I was being selfish.
Heroic Knight: So, before the night's over, I wanted to give you something.
Heroic Knight: Princess, maybe this won't mean much to you... I can't give you precious jewels, like the star shining on that tree.
Heroic Knight: But... I can give you my love. Princess, could I be your Christmas present? This year, and every year after?
Joan: And from then on, the Knight and the Princess rang in each new Christmas, together.
Teddy Bear: ......
Joan: Ayaa~ That ending is so romantic!!
Joan: After all those twists and turns and setbacks, you just knew she would find true love! Those are the rules!
Joan: Mm, that knight was really something...

Joan: Too bad I don't like such... average-looking men. 
Alas! What kind of woman am I?
Joan: Wait... why do I feel like I've said something like that before?
Joan: Does my writer keep track of all my old lines? Do you think... he's into me??
